<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="translational_fusion">Translational Fusion</a> - A <a href="#protein">protein</a> fusion where the two <a href="#protein">proteins</a> are <a href="#translation">translated</a> together. The coding sequences of <a href="#translation">translationally</a> fused <a href="#protein">proteins</a> are on the same <a href="#mrna">mRNA</a> and form a single <a href="#polypeptide">polypeptide</a> chain when <a href="#translation">translated</a>.